.TH "NAVIGATIONHISTORYENTRY.INDEX" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigationHistoryEntry.index \- NavigationHistoryEntry: index property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]index\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] interface returns the index of the
history entry in the history entries list (that is, the list returned by
\f[CR]Navigation.entries()\f[R]), or \f[CR]\-1\f[R] if the entry does
not appear in the list or if current document is not fully active.
.SH VALUE
A number representing the \f[CR]index\f[R] of the entry in the history
entries list, or \f[CR]\-1\f[R] if this item does not appear in the
list.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] current = navigation.currentEntry;
console.log(current.index);
.EE
